Fast-Data HTTP Guide
Tested on Rockwell PLC only
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click on "Fast-Data" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "HTTP".
4
Select the host to which you want to bind the HTTP server from the drop down
menu: "127.0.0.1" (localhost only) or 0.0.0.0 (all interfaces).
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Select the "HTTP Custom Port" checkbox if you want to use a custom port instead
of the default (8080).
6
Enter custom port number inside the new "Port number" field.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
The "HTTP Path" field defines the path where the HTTP server listens for incoming
requests.
8
Move to "File suffix".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Select the "Add file suffix" checkbox if you want to add a file suffix to the file name
when it's sent to the blob storage.
10
Enter the desired suffix inside the new "File suffix" field.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Move to "Blob settings".
12
The "Blob Settings" tab defines a match between the prefix of the file name
received from the a4GATE and the blob storage folder where the file will be sent. A
new row can be added to the tab by clicking on the "+" icon, an existing line can be
modified by clicking on the "pencil" icon or deleted by clicking on the "red trash"
icon.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
Careful, a single file can be sent only to one folder. The tab has a hierarchial order.
13
You can now click the "Save" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
14
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
15
Select the "HTTP service status" to disable the HTTP service. After this operation
you will be directed to the "Data Sender" page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
16
Select the "Fast Data HTTP service disabled" checkbox to enable HTTP service
again.
17
You can now return to the HTTP page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
18
Select the required option from "HTTP service commands" to start, stop or restart
the HTTP service.
19
Select the "Reboot Data Sender" checkbox to reboot the Data Sender. Click the
"Apply" button to start the reboot.
